1z8No2dF-HI.title: Pilates Core Strength - For a Strong, Functional Core - With Caity EP2 - eFit30
1z8No2dF-HI.description:
This Pilates Core Workout is designed for people who would like to improve their core strength - and it's also perfect for people who surf or skate. 

Visit our website for training downloads and workout ideas. www.efit30.com. 

Each month we have a free Workout Challenge. Check it out here: https://efit30.com/workout-challenge

Caity developed this Pilates video to help her surfing friends develop their core strength and loosen up their hips for surfing. 

How does Pilates help surfers? Surfers often suffer from lower back and shoulder injuries thanks to constant paddling and lying in the prone position. And maintaining a prolonged back extension can pinch the lower back area. Without abdominal strength and endurance, the tension in this area increases as you tire. 

Caity has put together a combination of Pilates exercises to target the muscles that ground your body to the board. Regular practice of this Pilates video will help train muscles get used to working with properly even when you're fatigued.

Why do Pilates? Body shaping or sculpting and improving your activation - and that in turn increases your calorie burn in every exercise you do.

Pilates helps improve the strength and tone of your muscles, especially around your midsection. This shapes your body and gives you a leaner appearance. 

Visit our website for training downloads and workout ideas. www.efit30.com

Learn the top 5 Supplements we recommend to help speed up your results: https://efit30.com/blog/5-supplements-to-speed-up-success

TJjsofXyzRI.title: Pilates, 100's Variation, Hard Core Workout for Abs, Arms & Cardio
TJjsofXyzRI.description:
Join our January Workout Challenge here: https://efit30.com/blog/january-workout-calendar

The Pilates 100 is one of the basic, staple Pilates exercises used to strengthen the abdominal muscles, build body stability and strengthen the lower back. The Pilates 100 also reinforces proper Pilates breathing techniques. 

One modification for the Pilates 100 is to keep your knees at a bent position the entire time. Alternatively if your hip flexors are bothering you, place your feet on the floor and practice the exercise with your legs down.

Use this video as a finisher to another workout or when you have five minutes to focus on core! 

Pilates doesn’t just give you strong abs, these amazing exercise also strengthen your deep postural muscles that support alignment and encourage you to stay strong, long and walking tall.

Join our free WORKOUT CHALLENGE today. For more information, https://efit30.com/workout-challenge

6GRJRAu9_VM.title: Pilates, Wake-up Workout, Core, Abs, Cardio, 25 mins
6GRJRAu9_VM.description:
Use this Pilates, wake-up workout to start your day. In the early morning when you have just rolled out of your comfy bed, your body isn't disturbed by the challenges of your day. You are free to make a good start. With morning Pilates exercises, you can feel any stiffness and address it properly. To open your chest with the spine twist, to release your back muscles with the shoulder bridge, to stretch all your body with the swimming exercise: Pilates literally helps you to listen to your body.

This new workout is 25 minutes long and will help you ease into your day refreshed. 

Why not make this a regular appointment you keep with yourself and join our Free Monthly Workout Challenge? https://efit30.com/workout-challenge

If you have been sitting all day then this the perfect remedy for poor posture. This short pilates workout targets the chest, upper back, shoulders and core. Good posture is not about sitting up straight, it is about moving well and creating balance in the body. By strengthening the muscles of the back and lengthening the muscles through the chest and neck, we allow the spine to reset and restore, open the chest and start to develop better posture. 
Pilates is a fantastic exercise option for busy people, as it features many full-body exercises that focus on core strength and all over body conditioning. 
In this short workout, we get the whole body working straight away, and we don't stop till the very end. 
With options for beginners and challenges for advanced practitioners, you will work the whole body safely and powerfully in under 30 mins. 

About re-run
"Pilates, Physio and running coaching combine to assist runners of all levels in achieving pain-free running. Work to balance your body in the studio and then take to the road with a graduated and structured plan towards your goals.
Your feet are in good hands."

The Superficial Back Line consists of a line of fascia that starts at the plantar surface (bottom) of the foot. It travels up the entire posterior (back) side of the body, moving up over the head and finishes at the brow bone.
 
The function of this line is to extend the body. It brings the body into an erect an upright position and gives it strength.
 
This line is considered to be the original primary curve of the body. As we develop from infancy with movements of extension (ie, raising the head and neck) we develop opposing curves that help create balance. These other curves are known as secondary curves.
 
The body is balanced from head to toe using the primary and secondary curves.
 
The secondary curves consist of the Neck curvature, lower back curvature, knee curvature and feet curvature.
 
Dysfunctions in the Superficial Back Line usually occur in these secondary curve regions.
 
Dysfunctions in the SBL can lead to many diferent injuries and generalized weakness that can perpetuate dysfunctions in other regions of the body.
 
Compensatory patterns can also develop and the strain through this fascial line can be directed by other fascial lines of pull.  
 
It is important to note that dysfunctions can occur anywhere along the fascial line and that it can create pain or symptoms far from the source.  Your Therapist is trained to assess and treat the dysfunctions.
 
Although the Therapist may not necessarily work over the area where you are feeling the greatest amount of pain, her intent is always to search for and treat the primary area of restriction.
 
Because fascia is all connected, treatment in one area will always affect another area. #eFit30 #fitness #yoga #Pilates #exercise #health

8u9BHjLb8TI.title: Pilates Flexibility, Increase your flexibility, Physiotherapy Tips,  Superficial Back Line
8u9BHjLb8TI.description:
The SBL is responsible for holding us upright. Our SBL mediates our posture. Small adhesions, tensions and injuries to the line can cause back pain, hamstring pain or tightness, or poor balance (the body can literally be pulled back on the feet so that most of the body weight is in the heels). A very tight or constricted SBL can lead to increased lumbar lordosis and an anterior pelvic tilt (increased low-back curve – the swayback posture), hyperextension of the knees, plantar fasciitis, and bone spurs. Weakness in the SBL can lead to an increased curve in the thoracic spine. Many of us westerners have a fairly weak back line, because of sitting in chairs, well… basically, since we were old enough to hold ourselves upright in a chair. This presents itself as the slouching posture. Difficulty sitting upright to meditate for even a few minutes may be a sign of weakness or tightness (or commonly, both) in the SBL.

Trevor Aung Than is AirYoga’s resident physiotherapist and movement specialist.  Trevor graduated from Curtin University in 2001 and owned his own physiotherapy clinic between 2005-09.  In 2009 Trevor took the position as head physiotherapist and trainer for the Cirque du Soleil show, ZAiA, in Macau, China.  This was Trevor’s first exposure to the circus world and he was hooked from day one.

Trevor has 11 years’ experience in the health and fitness industry and has a special passion for functional training, Pilates and movement conditioning.  Trevor also runs Circus Conditioning, specializing in small group fitness classes and movement therapy.

our full website is here

www.efit30.com

The Superficial Front Line 

The next myofascial meridian that we will examine is the Superficial Front Line (SFL).  The Superficial Front Line functionally balances the Superficial Back Line in the sagittal (anterior-posterior) plane.  As we saw earlier, the SBL acts to contract the back of the body and then stretches during forward bends.  The SFL, antagonistic to this, acts to contract the front of the body and then stretches during backbending activities.
The SFL begins on the dorsal surface of the toes through the short and long toe extensor muscles.  This includes the anterior crural compartment and the anterior tibialis muscle.  The boney station that the meridian attaches to is the tibial tuberosity. #eFit30 #fitness #yoga #Pilates #exercise #health

Bree Kirk-Burnnand from Happy Healthy Hoops​ breaks the world record for the most number of hoops spun. Watch the video here.

WHAT IS HOOPING?

Hooping is just something that kids do, right? Wrong. Hooping is actually a great full body workout and is brilliant fun to boot! Hooping has positive effects on your body and your mind. 

 http://www.happyhealthyhoops.com/

burns fat: you can burn approximately 210 calories per 30 minute session, the equivalent of a half hour boot camp or cardio boxing workout

tones muscle: hooping is a great core workout, but also tones your glutes, thighs, legs and arms.

increases your fitness: hooping is a great cardiovascular workout and can burn as many calories as running on a treadmill

improves your mood: hooping is laugh out loud fun so you forget you are even exercising!

improves your coordination: hooping is all about timing and rhythm and over time it will improve your coordination

improves flexibility: hooping requires significant motion especially in your spine which can help improve movement in your back after sitting at a desk all day - and help prevent back injuries

“Exercisers can expect similar results from hooping as they’d get from bootcamp classes” - American Council on Exercise

Increase your flexibility, agility, strength, lightness, mobility, power, endurance, coordination, mobility and speed through flow drills and movement patterns 

Athletic Performance: One of the unique aspects of Animal Movement training is that it is multi-planar, meaning that you are moving through multiple planes of motion, you are teaching your body to coordinate its movements as unison and bi laterally rather than compartmentalising.

Cardiovascular Training: You can choose various Animal Flow movement drills to achieve different cardio response. You can perform some explosive forms and switches that are very intense and challenge your aerobic and anaerobic energy system.

Stability: All of the animal movements place the body in a “two to four Pillar” position which is with hands and feet in contact with the ground. This position allows all of the stabilisation systems to be on and coordinating between each other. Everything from the wrists, shoulders, spine, hips and ankles. There is no joint that is left unchallenged! There is bi-lateral and plyometric exercises that are incorporated to hit all the muscle fibres and ligaments 

Mobility/Flexibility: One of the elements that’s most often overlooked in training programs is joint mobility or flexibility. The animal flow workouts pushes the body through movements that result in increased mobility and flexibility naturally. Stretching through movement, not isolation.

"Be as strong, agile and as light as you can"

JOIN US FOR OUR ANNUAL BALI YOGA RETREAT IN NUSA LEMBONGAN  15 – 20th October 2017
Join Donna from The Yoga Vine teaching team and immerse yourself in the luxury of 5 days of pure bliss with daily yoga, meditation and healthy meals on a tropical island just half an hour from Bali! Nusa Lembongan lies southeast of Bali and is accessible by boat and once you’re on this stunning island you won’t want to leave!
Each day will start with yoga and meditation allowing plenty of time to delve deeper into your practice, bliss out and rejuvenate. You’ll follow with a healthy western or traditional Indonesian breakfast and then the day is yours to do whatever you wish. There’s an abundance of water sports and the beach is just over the steps past the swimming pool, so you may just choose to lay around all day with a good book!
We reconvene in the late afternoon with a gentle restorative class such as yin yoga or myofascial release then we gather once more for a delicious gourmet dinner.  Our accomodation is simply stunning with 3 swimming pools, manicured gardens, gorgeous rooms overlooking the sea and friendly staff to cater to your every need. Don’t miss out! Our limit is 20 so we can offer a truly unique and intimate yoga experience!
THIS STUNNING RESORT IS ISLAND LUXURY AT IT’S VERY BEST!  PREPARE TO BE TRANSPORTED INTO A TROPICAL OASIS OF BLISS AND DELIGHT!

https://www.thelembongantraveller.com/portfolio_page/the-yoga-vine/

http://www.theyogavine.com.au/yoga-events/2017/1/12/yoga-retreat-14-21-october-2017

A quick half hour tune up for intermediate practitioners. A couple of advanced poses to try and a nice sweet warm down to savasana. Enjoy!

By Donna at the Yoga Vine Perth http://www.theyogavine.com.au/

My name is Rhyanna Van Leeuwarden and I am an experienced yoga instructor based in Perth, Western Australia. My passion is bringing balance, clarity, strength and joy to the day-to-day lives of everybody through the practice of yoga. Drawing on my strong anatomical knowledge and experience of yoga philosophy, my aim is to provide a safe place for students to discover their strength and flexibility both on and off the mat.

Initially learning yoga in Sydney, I began to develop my own self-practice whilst living in remote locations around Australia and Thailand. I completed my first official yoga teacher training in Singapore with Tirisula Yoga and recently completed my 500hr training at Absolute Yoga Academy in Thailand.

My passion for teaching is absolute and my classes are different to most. I invite you to come and experience one of my classes with a single class session if you are new or unsure. I believe in sharing yoga not only as a series of movements, but as a philosophy and a way of life.

May the light from your practice follow you throughout your journey~

dkaGUNcmUu8.title: Pilates Core Strength Intense Workout 30 Mins, Mat Routine, Stability + Flexibility
dkaGUNcmUu8.description:
This Pilates Core Workout is designed to strengthen and work out all four layers of abdominals. 

This workout is focused on the powerhouse which is the deepest layer of your abdominals, and will also actively work your transverse abdominals and well as your internal and external obliques, creating a flat, tightened and well-defined stomach. 

Not only does this make you look great, but it also builds strength through the powerhouse which will support your spine and posture.

JOIN US FOR OUR ANNUAL BALI YOGA RETREAT IN NUSA LEMBONGAN
15 – 20th October 2017
Join Donna from The Yoga Vine teaching team and immerse yourself in the luxury of 5 days of pure bliss with daily yoga, meditation and healthy meals on a tropical island just half an hour from Bali! Nusa Lembongan lies southeast of Bali and is accessible by boat and once you’re on this stunning island you won’t want to leave!
Each day will start with yoga and meditation allowing plenty of time to delve deeper into your practice, bliss out and rejuvenate. You’ll follow with a healthy western or traditional Indonesian breakfast and then the day is yours to do whatever you wish. There’s an abundance of water sports and the beach is just over the steps past the swimming pool, so you may just choose to lay around all day with a good book!
We reconvene in the late afternoon with a gentle restorative class such as yin yoga or myofascial release then we gather once more for a delicious gourmet dinner.  Our accomodation is simply stunning with 3 swimming pools, manicured gardens, gorgeous rooms overlooking the sea and friendly staff to cater to your every need. Don’t miss out! Our limit is 20 so we can offer a truly unique and intimate yoga experience!
THIS STUNNING RESORT IS ISLAND LUXURY AT IT’S VERY BEST!  PREPARE TO BE TRANSPORTED INTO A TROPICAL OASIS OF BLISS AND DELIGHT!

https://www.thelembongantraveller.com/portfolio_page/the-yoga-vine/

http://www.theyogavine.com.au/yoga-events/2017/1/12/yoga-retreat-14-21-october-2017
This 45 min class starts off with a dynamic VINYASA FLOW, gradually easing off to introduce a few strong balances. We finish in Lotus then a sweet savasana. Enjoy! 

Designed for those with a regular practice, you will flow, open and invert, so have fun!

By Donna at the Yoga Vine Perth http://www.theyogavine.com.au/
 
Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

In this series Andriana Elezovich (AIF Master Trainer Dip. Nutrition & Dietetics) demonstrates a simple series of exercises. These are part of a High Intensity Circuit Training Program or HICT there is an app to help you; the 7 Minute Fitness App it is free you can get it here;

bit.ly/1fpgwjh 

Full list of exercises here on our playlist  bit.ly/1bwHAKA 

How it works. This is only one example of an exercise that could be part of a 12-station HICT program. All exercises can be done with body weight and implements easily acquired in almost any setting (e.g., home, office, hotel room, etc.). The exercise order allows for a total body exercise to significantly increase the heart rate while the lower, upper, and core exercises function to maintain the increased heart rate while developing strength.

Exercises are performed for 30 seconds, with 10 seconds of transition time between bouts. Total time for the entire circuit workout is approximately 7 minutes. The circuit can be repeated 2 to 3 times.

JOIN US FOR OUR ANNUAL BALI YOGA RETREAT IN NUSA LEMBONGAN
15 – 20th October 2017
Join Donna from The Yoga Vine teaching team and immerse yourself in the luxury of 5 days of pure bliss with daily yoga, meditation and healthy meals on a tropical island just half an hour from Bali! Nusa Lembongan lies southeast of Bali and is accessible by boat and once you’re on this stunning island you won’t want to leave!
Each day will start with yoga and meditation allowing plenty of time to delve deeper into your practice, bliss out and rejuvenate. You’ll follow with a healthy western or traditional Indonesian breakfast and then the day is yours to do whatever you wish. There’s an abundance of water sports and the beach is just over the steps past the swimming pool, so you may just choose to lay around all day with a good book!
We reconvene in the late afternoon with a gentle restorative class such as yin yoga or myofascial release then we gather once more for a delicious gourmet dinner.  Our accomodation is simply stunning with 3 swimming pools, manicured gardens, gorgeous rooms overlooking the sea and friendly staff to cater to your every need. Don’t miss out! Our limit is 20 so we can offer a truly unique and intimate yoga experience!
THIS STUNNING RESORT IS ISLAND LUXURY AT IT’S VERY BEST!  PREPARE TO BE TRANSPORTED INTO A TROPICAL OASIS OF BLISS AND DELIGHT!

https://www.thelembongantraveller.com/portfolio_page/the-yoga-vine/

http://www.theyogavine.com.au/yoga-events/2017/1/12/yoga-retreat-14-21-october-2017
This is a 45min strong flow with a shoulder strengthening and inversion focused flow.  Designed for those with a regular Yoga practice, this sequence will spice up your day so be ready to flow, open up and enjoy! 

By Kate at the Yoga Vine Perth http://www.theyogavine.com.au/
 
Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

In this series Andriana Elezovich (AIF Master Trainer Dip. Nutrition & Dietetics) demonstrates a simple series of exercises. These are part of a High Intensity Circuit Training Program or HICT there is an app to help you; the 7 Minute Fitness App it is free you can get it here;

bit.ly/1fpgwjh 

Full list of exercises here on our playlist  bit.ly/1bwHAKA 

How it works. This is only one example of an exercise that could be part of a 12-station HICT program. All exercises can be done with body weight and implements easily acquired in almost any setting (e.g., home, office, hotel room, etc.). The exercise order allows for a total body exercise to significantly increase the heart rate while the lower, upper, and core exercises function to maintain the increased heart rate while developing strength.

Exercises are performed for 30 seconds, with 10 seconds of transition time between bouts. Total time for the entire circuit workout is approximately 7 minutes. The circuit can be repeated 2 to 3 times.

JOIN US FOR OUR ANNUAL BALI YOGA RETREAT IN NUSA LEMBONGAN
15 – 20th October 2017
Join Donna from The Yoga Vine teaching team and immerse yourself in the luxury of 5 days of pure bliss with daily yoga, meditation and healthy meals on a tropical island just half an hour from Bali! Nusa Lembongan lies southeast of Bali and is accessible by boat and once you’re on this stunning island you won’t want to leave!
Each day will start with yoga and meditation allowing plenty of time to delve deeper into your practice, bliss out and rejuvenate. You’ll follow with a healthy western or traditional Indonesian breakfast and then the day is yours to do whatever you wish. There’s an abundance of water sports and the beach is just over the steps past the swimming pool, so you may just choose to lay around all day with a good book!
We reconvene in the late afternoon with a gentle restorative class such as yin yoga or myofascial release then we gather once more for a delicious gourmet dinner.  Our accomodation is simply stunning with 3 swimming pools, manicured gardens, gorgeous rooms overlooking the sea and friendly staff to cater to your every need. Don’t miss out! Our limit is 20 so we can offer a truly unique and intimate yoga experience!
THIS STUNNING RESORT IS ISLAND LUXURY AT IT’S VERY BEST!  PREPARE TO BE TRANSPORTED INTO A TROPICAL OASIS OF BLISS AND DELIGHT!

https://www.thelembongantraveller.com/portfolio_page/the-yoga-vine/

http://www.theyogavine.com.au/yoga-events/2017/1/12/yoga-retreat-14-21-october-2017
This is a 45min strong flow with a focus on backbends, a little core work and hip openers. Designed for those with a regular Yoga practice, this sequence will spice up your day so be ready to flow, open up and enjoy! 

By Kate at the Yoga Vine Perth http://www.theyogavine.com.au/
 
Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

We recommend the resources on Live Lighter LOOK HERE

http://www.livelighter.com.au/


Full details for this routine are available at www.eFit30.com.au or on our main Channel

http://www.youtube.com/user/efit30

JOIN US FOR OUR ANNUAL BALI YOGA RETREAT IN NUSA LEMBONGAN
15 – 20th October 2017
Join Donna from The Yoga Vine teaching team and immerse yourself in the luxury of 5 days of pure bliss with daily yoga, meditation and healthy meals on a tropical island just half an hour from Bali! Nusa Lembongan lies southeast of Bali and is accessible by boat and once you’re on this stunning island you won’t want to leave!
Each day will start with yoga and meditation allowing plenty of time to delve deeper into your practice, bliss out and rejuvenate. You’ll follow with a healthy western or traditional Indonesian breakfast and then the day is yours to do whatever you wish. There’s an abundance of water sports and the beach is just over the steps past the swimming pool, so you may just choose to lay around all day with a good book!
We reconvene in the late afternoon with a gentle restorative class such as yin yoga or myofascial release then we gather once more for a delicious gourmet dinner.  Our accomodation is simply stunning with 3 swimming pools, manicured gardens, gorgeous rooms overlooking the sea and friendly staff to cater to your every need. Don’t miss out! Our limit is 20 so we can offer a truly unique and intimate yoga experience!
THIS STUNNING RESORT IS ISLAND LUXURY AT IT’S VERY BEST!  PREPARE TO BE TRANSPORTED INTO A TROPICAL OASIS OF BLISS AND DELIGHT!

https://www.thelembongantraveller.com/portfolio_page/the-yoga-vine/

http://www.theyogavine.com.au/yoga-events/2017/1/12/yoga-retreat-14-21-october-2017
This is a 45min strong flow for opening hips with some arm balancing and inversions to play with! Designed for those with a regular practice, you will flow, open and invert, so have fun!

By Donna at the Yoga Vine Perth http://www.theyogavine.com.au/
 
Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

2pJ8MeqRv3g.title: Better Flexibility for Yoga, Pilates, Tension and Integrity Lesson, Tensegrity
2pJ8MeqRv3g.description:
Learn about Tension and Integrity, Tensegrity, a balance of tension  Discover how the model displays strain on the body and helps to understand fascia.

Are you looking for better flexibility in your Yoga or Pilates practice? Trevor Aung Than B.Sc (Physio) has made a series of videos that explain from anatomy principals, how to release bound muscle tissue to make a noticeable difference to your practice by improving your flexibility. You will need to work at this for some months and watch the whole series to obtain the full benefits of this instruction.

This video from Trevor Aung Than B.Sc (Physio) explains Biotensegrity, a term coined by Dr Stephen Levin is the application of tensegrity principles to biologic structures.

About Trevor

Trevor worked as a physiotherapist for Cirque du Soleil and is now Head of Dancer Wellbeing at West Australian Ballet Company.
He also works at Circus Conditioning teaches educational workshops and functional fitness classes utilizing unconventional methods to efficiently train the body.  His methods encourage the body to be more mobile and resilient incorporating authentic movement, mobility training and fascial training techniques"

Other videos in this series

Superficial Front Line
Superficial Back Line
Lateral Line #eFit30 #fitness #yoga #Pilates #exercise #health

This is exercise number 4 in part 2 of the flexibility series. This will improve your flexibility for the Pilates book opening pose or other spine rotation poses.

Try these handy release techniques to get more out of your Pilates practice and increase flexibility.  These techniques are releasing the fascia, or connective tissue, in common areas where we become bound or glued.  By Trevor Aung Than B.Sc (Physio).  Trevor worked as a physiotherapist for Cirque du Soleil and is now Head of Dancer Wellbeing at West Australian Ballet Company.

Learn more at www.circusconditioning.com.  

Trevor from Circus Conditioning teaches educational workshops and functional fitness classes utilizing unconventional methods to efficiently train the body.  His methods encourage the body to be more mobile and resilient incorporating authentic movement, mobility training and fascial training techniques"

Don't forget you can add more or just keep going a the end of this video! With our superset routines, you can do 15, 30 or 45 minutes by adding in more eFit30 routines at the end of this, This is part of the superset series.

Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

qRX58AoL2wI.title: How to Increase Your Yoga Flexibility - Trikonasana or Triangle Pose
qRX58AoL2wI.description:
This is Part 2 of the Yoga flexibility series. Try these handy release techniques to get more out of your yoga practice and increase flexibility.  These techniques are releasing the fascia, or connective tissue, in common areas where we become bound or glued.  By Trevor Aung Than B.Sc (Physio).  Learn more at www.circusconditioning.com.  

Trevor from Circus Conditioning teaches educational workshops and functional fitness classes utilizing unconventional methods to efficiently train the body.  His methods encourage the body to be more mobile and resilient incorporating authentic movement, mobility training and fascial training techniques"

Don't forget you can add more or just keep going a the end of this video! With our superset routines, you can do 15, 30 or 45 minutes by adding in more eFit30 routines at the end of this, This is part of the superset series, Choose to do 15, 30, or 45 minutes of exercise! You can do this power workout once for 15 minutes, twice for 30 minutes or at the end of this we provide other suggested routines to build in 45 minutes! Your choice!
 
Remember to always warm up before exercise and stretch after exercise. There is an eFIt30 video specifically about stretching.

This Yoga practice is designed to allow you to let go of and be receptive to whatever is coming your way today. 

By Lara Dwyer http://www.sukhayogaaustralia.com.au/

Lara from "Sukha Yoga" teaches Vinyasa Yoga. A Vinyasa yoga class involves linking asana's (body posture) and breath in a connective sequenced flow. At Sukha Yoga, we invite you to practice in a way that is comfortable for your body so that you can be completely present and aware of how you like to move. The increased interest and attention to ourselves on how we move and breathe encourages us to slow down and in turn teaches us to become more aware, on and off the yoga mat.

This is a 15 minute Plyometrics Exercise Session with Jess from Babes on the run. This is an intense routine!

You will need a mat.

What Are Plyometrics?

Unlike typical strength training exercises that involve long, slow movements designed to increase muscular strength and mass, plyometric exercises involve quick, explosive movements designed to increase speed and power.

A plyometric exercise consists of three phases. The first is a rapid muscle lengthening movement called the eccentric phase. Second comes a short resting period called the amortization phase. Finally, the athlete engages in an explosive muscle shortening movement called the concentric phase. The athlete repeats this three-part cycle as quickly as he can.

The goal of plyometric exercises is to decrease the amount of time in-between the eccentric and concentric movements. By reducing the time in-between these two movements, a man can become faster and more powerful.

This Vinyasa Evening flow Yoga practice is designed to allow you to release your shoulders especially if you have been sat in front of a computer all day!

By Lara Dwyer http://www.sukhayogaaustralia.com.au/

Lara from "Sukha Yoga" teaches Vinyasa Yoga. A Vinyasa yoga class involves linking asana's (body posture) and breath in a connective sequenced flow. At Sukha Yoga, we invite you to practice in a way that is comfortable for your body so that you can be completely present and aware of how you like to move. The increased interest and attention to ourselves on how we move and breathe encourages us to slow down and in turn teaches us to become more aware, on and off the yoga mat.
